                                                                                                               Hyundai cars to cost more
          OUR CORRESPONDENT                              
	New Delhi, Feb. 13: Hyundai Motor India Ltd has increased the prices of some of its models with immediate effect to offset a rise in input cost.        
	Maruti Suzuki India, General Motors, Toyota and Ford Motor India had also hiked prices recently.         
	The price hike is primarily due to a rise in input cost and ranges from 1.2 per cent to 3 per cent, the company said.        
	After the revision, the Santro will be costlier by Rs 3,601-Rs 5,163. The premium compact car i10 will be dearer by Rs 3,974-Rs 7,637, while its entry level sedan Accent will cost Rs 14,636 more.        
	For Verna  the mid-sized Sedan  Hyundai will be charging between Rs 6.37 lakh and Rs 8.65 lakh. The price of the Sonata remains unchanged.                                                                                                                                       
